  "prompt": "Why doesn't Wetransfer give the shared file links immediately on the screen after the upload completes, like SendSpace does?",
  "response": "WeTransfer and other file sharing services may have different approaches to providing file links due to how their systems are designed and user experience strategies. Here are some possible reasons why WeTransfer may not display the shared file links immediately after upload:\n\n1. **Verification and Processing**: After files are uploaded, WeTransfer might take extra time to ensure the files are securely stored and free of any issues. This processing time can delay the generation of immediate links.\n\n2. **Email-based Systems**: WeTransfer typically uses an email-based sharing system where the download link is sent directly to the recipient's email. This process may not necessitate immediate on-screen links like some other services.\n\n3. **User Experience Design**: The design philosophy of WeTransfer might prioritize simplicity and minimal steps, aiming to keep the process straightforward without additional options that might confuse some users.\n\n4. **Security Concerns**: Delaying the presentation of a link can be a part of security protocol to ensure that only legitimate, fully uploaded files are shared, minimizing incomplete or corrupted file sharing incidents.\n\n5. **Server Load Management**: To manage server loads effectively, WeTransfer might prefer to queue link generation at a second stage after uploads, balancing load across their infrastructure.\n\nEach file sharing service, including SendSpace, has its own method for handling uploads, which reflects its priorities in terms of speed, security, and user interface design.",
